00:57:35.609 --> 00:57:36.901
Gentlemen.

802
00:57:38.987 --> 00:57:41.072
And as soon
as he met my boss,


803
00:57:41.198 --> 00:57:43.157
he didn't know to be intimidated by her,

804
00:57:43.241 --> 00:57:44.784
and the next thing you know...

805
00:57:44.910 --> 00:57:46.911
Little man, what do you think of that?

806
00:57:47.537 --> 00:57:48.788
Not much.

807
00:57:48.872 --> 00:57:50.664
Well, that's honest.

808
00:57:50.749 --> 00:57:51.791
Timothy's very honest, ma'am.

809
00:57:51.875 --> 00:57:56.045
That was done by a renowned artist
at great expense.


810
00:57:56.129 --> 00:57:57.797
I would have done it for free.

811
00:57:59.132 --> 00:58:01.300
Are you suggesting
you could do it better?


812
00:58:02.010 --> 00:58:03.177
I can try.

813
00:58:04.554 --> 00:58:06.555
Well, let's find out.

814
00:58:08.100 --> 00:58:10.935
May I just remind you,
ma'am, as his parent,


815
00:58:11.019 --> 00:58:12.061
that he is only ten years old, and...

816
00:58:12.145 --> 00:58:13.479
Don't you have somewhere to be?

817
00:58:13.563 --> 00:58:14.855
Of course I do, but...

818
00:58:15.816 --> 00:58:16.982
- Shoo.
- Okay.


819
00:59:31.725 --> 00:59:32.725
Oh!

820
00:59:35.103 --> 00:59:36.896
Oh, sweetie.

821
00:59:37.814 --> 00:59:40.649
Oh, it's beautiful. It's amazing.

822
00:59:40.775 --> 00:59:42.067
It's amazing.

823
00:59:44.070 --> 00:59:46.113
Oh, no, no, no.
Erase that.


824
00:59:46.364 --> 00:59:47.698
Why?

825
00:59:49.242 --> 00:59:53.871
It turns out, Timothy
was Picasso with a pencil.


826
00:59:53.955 --> 00:59:56.248
So he had
all the qualities you imagined?


827
00:59:56.416 --> 00:59:57.416
Oh, yes.

828
00:59:57.667 --> 01:00:00.794
Yeah, well,
including honest to a fault.


829
01:00:13.099 --> 01:00:15.351
He couldn't help
but draw her exactly as he saw her.


830
01:00:15.435 --> 01:00:16.519
Yeah.

831
01:00:17.020 --> 01:00:19.855
It included an unfortunate
thatch of chin hair.


832
01:00:19.940 --> 01:00:20.940
Mmm.

833
01:00:27.197 --> 01:00:30.658
So, what else aren't you telling me?

834
01:00:32.911 --> 01:00:33.953
Tell her.

835
01:00:34.371 --> 01:00:35.746
Hmm?

836
01:00:35.956 --> 01:00:37.081
I'm waiting.

837
01:00:37.749 --> 01:00:40.042
Sometimes you wear
plaids and stripes that clash.


838
01:00:40.794 --> 01:00:42.127
Hmm.

839
01:00:42.337 --> 01:00:45.089
Your one joke that
you always tell, it's not funny.


840
01:00:46.383 --> 01:00:48.884
No one can appreciate the art in here

841
01:00:48.969 --> 01:00:50.678
because everything
that is special and beautiful,


842
01:00:50.762 --> 01:00:52.263
no one can see
because the curtains are so thick


843
01:00:52.347 --> 01:00:54.348
that the light can't get in.

844
01:00:54.432 --> 01:00:56.850
Not to mention, if someone has a child

845
01:00:56.935 --> 01:00:59.895
who just is born or appears,

846
01:01:00.272 --> 01:01:02.314
say congratulations with a smile.

847
01:01:02.440 --> 01:01:04.316
Say something nice.

848
01:01:04.985 --> 01:01:06.235
I wanted to love you,

849
01:01:06.319 --> 01:01:07.903
and I have tried
so hard to like you.

850
01:01:07.988 --> 01:01:10.823
But if someone asked me to be
a pallbearer at your funeral,


851
01:01:10.907 --> 01:01:14.326
I would tell them not by
the hair of my chinny-chin-chin.


852
01:01:14.869 --> 01:01:15.995
And furthermore...

853
01:01:16.079 --> 01:01:18.122
- Cindy lost herjob.
- I lost my job.


854
01:01:21.001 --> 01:01:23.836
I didn't regret most of what I said.

855
01:01:24.921 --> 01:01:26.213
But you lost yourjob.

856
01:01:28.216 --> 01:01:29.758
Make sure all the pencils are good.

857
01:01:29.843 --> 01:01:31.719
So things were going to get harder.

858
01:01:31.803 --> 01:01:33.512
But at least I still had myjob.

859
01:01:33.763 --> 01:01:34.972
Yes, he did.

860
01:01:35.473 --> 01:01:38.183
They go in this box.
They go on a little pencil vacation.


861
01:01:38.268 --> 01:01:39.310
And what did you say about

862
01:01:39.394 --> 01:01:41.103
having Timothy with you that day?

863
01:01:41.187 --> 01:01:43.022
- Oh, right.
- That's a lot of trees.


864
01:01:43.773 --> 01:01:45.065
I couldn't help but feel...

865
01:01:45.150 --> 01:01:46.191
Mind if I have one?

866
01:01:46.359 --> 01:01:47.484
...anything was possible.

867
01:01:47.819 --> 01:01:49.194
You want another one?
You want a yellow one?


868
01:01:49.279 --> 01:01:51.155
We got this... 
You see, we got a whole...

869
01:01:51.239 --> 01:01:53.157
- Right back.
- Good luck, Dad.


870
01:01:53.533 --> 01:01:55.826
So Jim gave it his best shot.

871
01:01:55.952 --> 01:01:57.828
Sir? How you doing?

872
01:01:59.456 --> 01:02:00.831
- Huh?
- Do you have a minute?


873
01:02:01.207 --> 01:02:02.207
No.

874
01:02:04.044 --> 01:02:07.212
Oh, hell. Why not?
Turns out we may all get the axe.


875
01:02:08.381 --> 01:02:09.381
What?

876
01:02:09.466 --> 01:02:11.383
Then I think we got nothing to lose.

877
01:02:11.468 --> 01:02:14.303
What if we made
a new kind of pencil?

878
01:02:46.461 --> 01:02:49.338
Come on, Erasers!
Come on! Come on!


879
01:02:49.422 --> 01:02:52.007
Push up the field! 
Push up the field!

880
01:02:52.092 --> 01:02:55.469
Don't pass it!
How do you score if you pass it!


881
01:02:56.262 --> 01:02:58.597
Kick it! Kick the ball!

882
01:02:59.599 --> 01:03:01.016
- Mom! I'm so thirsty.
- What are you doing?


883
01:03:01.184 --> 01:03:03.560
No, no, no. Get back
on D. Back on D!

884
01:03:06.981 --> 01:03:08.065
Come on!

885
01:03:09.484 --> 01:03:12.986
I saw your car.
Didn't know the kid was a player.


886
01:03:13.071 --> 01:03:14.363
What position? Striker?

887
01:03:14.447 --> 01:03:15.489
Uh...

888
01:03:15.573 --> 01:03:18.409
Well, he's taking a break right now.

889
01:03:18.493 --> 01:03:20.953
Oh, well, I got time.

890
01:03:21.955 --> 01:03:23.205
It might be a while.

891
01:03:25.208 --> 01:03:26.917
You know, I'm impressed, Dad.

892
01:03:27.544 --> 01:03:29.128
You never really came to my games.

893
01:03:29.295 --> 01:03:33.132
No. I came.
You were always on the bench.


894
01:03:33.967 --> 01:03:37.428
Come on, Luke.
Find your man. Find your man!


895
01:03:37.637 --> 01:03:38.971
You got to want it!

896
01:03:39.055 --> 01:03:40.180
Oh, here we go.

897
01:03:40.306 --> 01:03:42.057
Come on, I want to see some fight!

898
01:03:42.183 --> 01:03:43.559
To keep you hydrated, sir.

899
01:03:45.019 --> 01:03:46.103
Thank you.

900
01:03:48.398 --> 01:03:49.857
He's a water boy.

901
01:03:51.067 --> 01:03:52.192
No. Dad,

902
01:03:52.277 --> 01:03:55.279
actually, I'm working
on all aspects of his game right now.


903
01:03:57.157 --> 01:03:58.323
And you know what...

904
01:03:58.491 --> 01:04:01.118
Come on, Erasers.
Keep your head in the game.


905
01:04:01.202 --> 01:04:02.327
Let's go, Bobby! Let's go!

906
01:04:02.412 --> 01:04:03.912
Good pass. Good pass.

907
01:04:07.333 --> 01:04:09.251
- All right.
- Yeah. Yeah.


908
01:04:10.003 --> 01:04:11.336
Good eye! Good eye!

909
01:04:11.421 --> 01:04:12.671
Talk to each other!

910
01:04:12.922 --> 01:04:15.424
Erasers, talk to each other!

911
01:04:15.508 --> 01:04:17.926
That's your house, Philip!

912
01:04:18.011 --> 01:04:19.636
Don't let nothing in there!
That's your house!


913
01:04:19.763 --> 01:04:20.637
That's your house!

914
01:04:27.479 --> 01:04:29.521
All this time, it felt like

915
01:04:29.606 --> 01:04:32.191
there was something
Timothy wasn't telling us.


916
01:04:41.326 --> 01:04:44.119
And he was spending
far too much time with that girl.


917
01:04:44.204 --> 01:04:45.954
Was it a problem for you?

918
01:04:47.707 --> 01:04:49.416
Well,
they were up to something,


919
01:04:49.501 --> 01:04:50.459
and we didn't know what.

920
01:04:52.337 --> 01:04:54.296
Can you teach me to do that thing?

921
01:04:54.380 --> 01:04:55.964
You know, that you do with your arms

922
01:04:56.049 --> 01:04:57.633
and you put your
head up in the sun.

923
01:04:57.717 --> 01:04:59.051
Well, first, find the light, all right?

924
01:04:59.135 --> 01:05:00.135
Okay.

925
01:05:00.220 --> 01:05:04.973
Just absorb it.
Just soak it in. Think "tree."


926
01:05:06.476 --> 01:05:08.268
- Do you feel it?
- Yeah, I feel it.


927
01:05:09.395 --> 01:05:10.479
Nice.

928
01:05:12.023 --> 01:05:13.607
Maybe you should show your birthmark,

929
01:05:13.691 --> 01:05:15.275
because people might like it.

930
01:05:15.360 --> 01:05:16.360
I don't know.

931
01:05:16.444 --> 01:05:19.238
We didn't know
what he was doing with the girl.


932
01:05:19.322 --> 01:05:20.906
It was fine if he
wanted to have a secret

933
01:05:20.990 --> 01:05:23.075
as long as he shared it with us.

934
01:05:25.370 --> 01:05:27.538
So Cindy did
what she thought was best.


935
01:05:36.923 --> 01:05:39.967
Hey!

936
01:05:44.013 --> 01:05:45.097
We need to talk.

937
01:05:45.181 --> 01:05:46.473
Okay, let's talk.

938
01:05:47.600 --> 01:05:48.725
Well, can you wait?

939
01:05:50.270 --> 01:05:51.395
Fine.

940
01:05:54.607 --> 01:05:58.777
I don't think that
you're the best influence on my son,


941
01:05:59.028 --> 01:06:01.029
and I want you
to tell me what you know about him.


942
01:06:01.114 --> 01:06:02.281
I know a lot.

943
01:06:02.365 --> 01:06:03.490
I thought so.

944
01:06:04.284 --> 01:06:05.701
So you know that he's got...

945
01:06:07.704 --> 01:06:09.246
You know that he's different.

946
01:06:09.372 --> 01:06:11.707
Yeah. It's what I like about him.

947
01:06:13.501 --> 01:06:15.294
Well, it's a hard
world to be different in.

948
01:06:16.421 --> 01:06:17.796
And I don't want him to be hurt.

949
01:06:18.256 --> 01:06:20.257
By you or anyone. 
I won't let it happen.

950
01:06:20.383 --> 01:06:21.466
That's good.

951
01:06:23.720 --> 01:06:25.178
What is this?

952
01:06:26.431 --> 01:06:28.307
He's going to be misunderstood.

953
01:06:29.767 --> 01:06:31.768
Lots of people hate anything different.

954
01:06:33.688 --> 01:06:35.355
I wish it wasn't this way, but

955
01:06:36.190 --> 01:06:38.609
I wish a lot of things. I wish...

956
01:06:52.749 --> 01:06:56.668
It took my breath away,
this world they created.


957
01:06:59.631 --> 01:07:01.089
I was wrong

958
01:07:01.633 --> 01:07:04.593
about this, this girl.

959
01:07:16.189 --> 01:07:17.481
You did this?

960
01:07:17.607 --> 01:07:20.317
Yeah. Timothy and I did it together.

961
01:07:21.361 --> 01:07:22.444
I had made a mistake.

962
01:07:22.528 --> 01:07:23.612
We made lots of mistakes.

963
01:07:23.696 --> 01:07:26.698
Yeah, we made mistakes
trying to fix our mistakes.


964
01:07:26.783 --> 01:07:28.533
Isn't that how you know you're a parent?

965
01:07:32.372 --> 01:07:34.414
You seem to forget
what the object is here.


966
01:07:34.540 --> 01:07:36.333
You need to persuade us.

967
01:07:36.417 --> 01:07:38.710
Tell me, what would you do differently?

968
01:07:40.463 --> 01:07:41.880
We'd make better mistakes?

969
01:07:42.131 --> 01:07:43.548
- Better?
- Different. New.


970
01:07:43.633 --> 01:07:44.758
New mistakes.

971
01:07:44.842 --> 01:07:47.135
That's... That's what we'd do.

972
01:07:47.220 --> 01:07:48.303
Yeah.

973
01:07:49.472 --> 01:07:51.723
Put your
heart into it, Erasers!


974
01:07:52.892 --> 01:07:54.309
Smarten up out there.

975
01:07:54.394 --> 01:07:55.560
Bobby.

976
01:07:57.397 --> 01:07:58.605
The most amazing thing happened.

977
01:07:58.690 --> 01:08:00.816
I woke up this morning
and I started to draw again.


978
01:08:00.900 --> 01:08:03.485
Oh, God! It must be so nice to
have time to waste.


979
01:08:03.569 --> 01:08:04.569
It was like coming home.

980
01:08:04.654 --> 01:08:07.155
My three are so busy with
their second languages,


981
01:08:07.240 --> 01:08:08.240
their public service work...

982
01:08:08.324 --> 01:08:09.866
Oh, and their upcoming music recital.

983
01:08:09.951 --> 01:08:11.660
Your presence is expected.

984
01:08:11.744 --> 01:08:14.830
Let's go, Erasers! Come on!

985
01:08:17.834 --> 01:08:19.543
Brenda's freaking me out.

986
01:08:21.671 --> 01:08:22.921
What's wrong?

987
01:08:24.841 --> 01:08:26.591
If you're on the bench now,

988
01:08:26.968 --> 01:08:29.386
you'll be on the
bench of life later on.

989
01:08:29.470 --> 01:08:31.388
Jim, that is your father talking.

990
01:08:31.514 --> 01:08:32.889
Coach. Coach!

991
01:08:33.391 --> 01:08:34.850
Put Green in!

992
01:08:35.560 --> 01:08:36.685
Come on.

993
01:08:36.769 --> 01:08:38.395
Good, Coach. Thank you.

994
01:08:38.479 --> 01:08:39.688
What are you doing? No, no, no. Jim...

995
01:08:39.772 --> 01:08:40.814
Put...

996
01:08:42.608 --> 01:08:43.775
What's going on?

997
01:08:44.777 --> 01:08:46.862
Oh, great.
Now he's going to do that again.


998
01:08:46.946 --> 01:08:48.363
What?

999
01:08:48.448 --> 01:08:51.199
He's going to uncross his arms,
crack his knuckles,


1000
01:08:51.284 --> 01:08:52.409
then he will turn and go.

1001
01:08:52.493 --> 01:08:53.535
Yep.

1002
01:08:53.619 --> 01:08:55.328
It's fine that he did that to me,

1003
01:08:55.413 --> 01:08:56.788
but now he's doing it to Timothy.

1004
01:08:57.331 --> 01:08:58.457
Hey, Jim...

1005
01:08:58.624 --> 01:09:00.417
Look. Look.

1006
01:09:03.546 --> 01:09:04.713
Here, Grandpa Jim.

1007
01:09:05.798 --> 01:09:07.716
You know
what I feel really good about?


1008
01:09:07.800 --> 01:09:09.760
Bart and I are just grateful
that our kids' school


1009
01:09:09.844 --> 01:09:11.636
has a gifted and talented program.

1010
01:09:12.513 --> 01:09:13.889
Did you know Timothy is gifted?

1011
01:09:13.973 --> 01:09:15.307
How so?

1012
01:09:15.808 --> 01:09:16.850
Well...

1013
01:09:17.977 --> 01:09:19.978
He always finds the bright side.

1014
01:09:20.313 --> 01:09:22.814
He never gives up
and he has a good heart.


1015
01:09:22.982 --> 01:09:24.858
That will get you into college.

1016
01:09:27.570 --> 01:09:29.529
- He's a great artist.
- Look where that got you.


1017
01:09:29.614 --> 01:09:30.697
Get open!

1018
01:09:30.823 --> 01:09:33.575
Brenda, I have to say, I am...

1019
01:09:33.659 --> 01:09:34.951
What? I'm listening.

1020
01:09:35.912 --> 01:09:36.995
He's musical.

1021
01:09:38.831 --> 01:09:40.332
- Really?
- Yeah.


1022
01:09:41.501 --> 01:09:42.876
What instruments does he play?

1023
01:09:45.963 --> 01:09:48.507
"He's musical?"
What possessed you to even say that?


1024
01:09:48.674 --> 01:09:50.592
She just kept bragging
about how her kids could do this,


1025
01:09:50.676 --> 01:09:51.718
her kids could do that.

1026
01:09:51.803 --> 01:09:54.763
So Cindy's sister
has this yearly family concert


1027
01:09:54.847 --> 01:09:56.348
that we never seem to miss.

1028
01:09:56.432 --> 01:09:58.600
If I'd known
what she was going to pull that day,


1029
01:09:58.684 --> 01:09:59.684
we never would have shown up.

1030
01:10:15.034 --> 01:10:17.536
Thank you. Thank you.

1031
01:10:18.371 --> 01:10:19.412
Brilliant.

1032
01:10:19.539 --> 01:10:22.833
Thank you. This year
we are going to dispense


1033
01:10:22.917 --> 01:10:24.793
with our traditional encore.

1034
01:10:24.877 --> 01:10:25.919
Oh!

1035
01:10:26.045 --> 01:10:29.756
Because we have a very special treat.

1036
01:10:29.841 --> 01:10:35.053
Sit back and enjoy
the musical stylings of Timothy Green!


1037
01:10:35.763 --> 01:10:37.889
You know what?
We're running late to something.


1038
01:10:37.974 --> 01:10:39.391
Go ahead and do the encore because...

1039
01:10:39.517 --> 01:10:41.726
No, Mom, it's okay. It's fine, Mom.

1040
01:10:43.020 --> 01:10:44.020
Um, Timothy?

1041
01:10:44.105 --> 01:10:45.438
- Hey, pal.
- Hey.


1042
01:10:45.523 --> 01:10:46.565
It's okay.

1043
01:11:02.707 --> 01:11:04.666
Just get him, baby. Just go.

1044
01:11:05.543 --> 01:11:06.835
Just get him. Get him.

1045
01:11:08.588 --> 01:11:09.713
Just go get him.

1046
01:11:09.797 --> 01:11:11.089
Hey, pal?

1047
01:11:34.780 --> 01:11:38.867
All my friends know the low rider

1048
01:11:41.787 --> 01:11:45.790
The low rider is a little higher

1049
01:12:09.815 --> 01:12:10.982
Yeah!

1050
01:12:22.036 --> 01:12:23.036
Yeah!

1051
01:12:23.454 --> 01:12:24.746
Can we go back and do it again?

1052
01:12:24.830 --> 01:12:25.956
No.

1053
01:12:26.040 --> 01:12:27.582
I don't think we'll be invited back.

1054
01:12:27.667 --> 01:12:29.751
But it doesn't matter
because you were great.


1055
01:12:29.835 --> 01:12:30.919
You rock, buddy.

1056
01:12:31.003 --> 01:12:32.754
It felt great to rock.

1057
01:12:32.838 --> 01:12:34.839
It felt great to
have a kid who rocked.

1058
01:12:35.925 --> 01:12:37.133
- Good night.
- Good night.


1059
01:12:37.927 --> 01:12:39.219
It was all you.

1060
01:12:39.512 --> 01:12:40.887
And us, but mostly you.

